Clicking the "Stop watching page" link at the bottom of the notification emails Confluence sends out leads the user to an "HTTP Status 401" error page. (see attached screenshot)

The issue seems to be when the user is not logged in. If the user is logged in, no matter if as the same user or as a different user than the one who received the email, it goes to the Watches page and works fine.

h3. Analysis

When the confluence-notification generates the jwt token which includes the qsh or query hash string, it uses the url below to get the qsh - *e6b5ebfe517835a100613994220541e29e1f210782a692197d54cf2f09df1079*,
{code:none}
https://learn.mdsol.com/users/removepagenotification.action?pageId=104701483&src=mail&src.mail.timestamp=1493941205456&src.mail.notification=com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-notifications-batch-plugin%3Abatching-notification&src.mail.recipient=ff80808140c6b55e0140c6b59e3e0402&src.mail.action=stop-watching
{code}
However, confluence is checking the qsh value against the url below because of the login action, hence the error msg
{code:none}
https://learn.mdsol.com/login.action?os_destination=/users/removepagenotification.action?pageId=104701483&src=mail&src.mail.timestamp=1493941205456&src.mail.notification=com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-notifications-batch-plugin%3Abatching-notification&src.mail.recipient=ff80808140c6b55e0140c6b59e3e0402&src.mail.action=stop-watching
{code}

h3. Workaround

Copy the URL and remove the 'jwt' token from it. Then, it will send the user to the login screen and after signing in, it will properly load the page watchers section in his profile.

In documentation that is covering [update of license|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Managing+your+Confluence+License#ManagingyourConfluenceLicense-Updatingyourlicense], we should include a note indicating, that after pressing {{SAVE}} on an instance without active internet connection, the page may not refresh (spinning wheel), however the procedure is still successful. This can cause confusion, even thought after a refresh it works well.

 
{panel:title=Applying license without active internet connectivity}
License can be updated even without internet connection, but please note that page will take some time to refresh.
{panel}
